  "title": "Error when running linter",
  "body": "When I try to run `npm run lint`, I have the following error:\n\n```\nError: algolia:\n        Configuration for rule \"no-cond-assign\" is invalid:\n        Severity should be one of the following: 0 = off, 1 = warning, 2 = error (you passed \"error\").\n```\n\nSame error occurs if I try to use `\"eslint-config-algolia\": \"^5.1.0\"` in another project. Looks like the syntax (now?) expect you to pass `2` instead of `error` in the eslint config.\n",
